cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper proposes a novel framework of neural networks and temporal point processes for predicting the temporal distribution of human activities in streaming data. The paper also extends the model to a joint estimation framework for predicting the timing, spatial location, and category of the activity simultaneously. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with sequential data and temporal dynamics, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible sub-categories.
